post_text: Glamping Comes to South GA! Towns Bluff Park and Heritage Center/RV Park and Campground in Hazlehurst now have 2 Yurts available in the RV Campground. Each Yurt will sleep up to 6 with a queen bed, full/single bunk bed & sleeper sofa. The Yurts have insulated walls & ceiling and have a heater/air conditioner unit. The Yurts have a wrap around deck, skylight with ceiling fan & an outdoor sink. The Yurt campsite has a picnic table & fire ring. They are located a short distance from the bath-house. Rates start at $65/night. Bed sheets are available for a small additional fee or you can bring your own sheets or sleeping bags. Call 912-379-9303 for reservations or more information. Let's Go Glamping!

post_text:
Be sure to mark the weekend of April 24, 25 & 26 for the Three Rivers Paddle & Broxton Rocks Tour. Hosted by the Hazlehurst-Jeff Davis Co. GA Board of Tourism & Towns Bluff Park and Heritage Center/RV Park and Campground and sponsored by the The Georgia Conservancy & Georgia Canoe Association. Registration is available online at the link below or can be done Friday 4/24 at Towns Bluff Park. Saturday, 4/25, will be a 14 mile paddle along the Ocmulgee thru the confluence with the Oconee and onto the Mighty Altamaha River. Sunday, 4/25, will be 2-3 mile hike thru Broxton Rocks. There are full packages that include camping at Towns Bluff RV Park. Day pass for the paddle & hike only is $30/person. You can bring your own canoe or kayak or rental canoes will be avaiable for $25/person or $50 per boat. See the link below for all the details.
http://www.georgiaconservancy.org/three-rivers-paddle

Come join us at Towns Bluff RV Park & Heritage Center on the Altamaha River, March 7, 2015 from 9:00 a.m. until 11:00 a.m. for a bird walk identifying the different bird species living on the park. Towns Bluff is located 8 miles east of Hazlehurst, GA off US 221. Limited number of binoculars are available, so please bring your own.
Birding programs will be offered each Saturday in March. Information on the other upcoming programs will be posted two weeks prior to each weekend. For further information call the Heritage Center at 912-379-9303.

We have really outstanding response from visitors coming in this weekend for the Three Rivers Paddle at Towns Bluff Park and Heritage Center/RV Park and Campground. It looks like we may have a need for a couple more canoes than our outfitter has available. If anyone has a canoe or tow they would be willing to loan us for the weekend, please let me know.

Also, if anyone has a pontoon boat & would like to volunteer to be our supply/safety boat on Saturday, please let me know. I will cover the cost of gas.

Thanks!

post_text: What a great weekend for Peaches to the Beaches. Nice warm, sunny weather & huge crowds. Our hotels & restaurants were full & other businesses along Hwy 341 were booming. Special thanks to Mike (Bird) Lynn, Bruce Johns & the staff at the Jeff Davis Recreation Dept for all the help getting the vendor site prepared & cleaned up. Thanks also the the City of Hazlehurst & Jeff Davis Co. for getting the parking lot at the rec dept ready for the crowds after the rain. Also, to the Police & Sheriff depts for all the extra work with traffic & security. We have hundreds of people tell us that Hazlehurst has the best setup of any place along the 200+ mile route. It takes great teamwork to pull off something this big & do it right.

post_text: Dal Cannady will once again be walking 97 miles in 7 days to raise money for the American Red Cross. He will be leaving Hazlehurst Wal-Mart on Thursday, February 27th promptly at 7:00a.m. The Chamber of Commerce would like to show our support for this worthy cause and have as many people as possible be on hand to encourage him as he leaves on his journey to Baxley. The Chamber challenges you to donate at least $10 to the American Red Cross. The plans are to present Mr. Cannady a donation from our community before he departs on Thursday morning so if you would like to be included in the donation from the Chamber, please make your check payable to the American Red Cross and bring by the Chamber office by Wednesday afternoon at 5:00pm.

Jeff Davis Ledger
January 28, 2014 at 11:09 AM ·

Jeff Davis County Schools
December 2, 2013 at 2:44 PM ·

The Jacket Theatre Company (JDH Drama Club) proudly presents this year’s Winter Play, “Headin’ for the Hills” by Le Roma Greth. The play will be performed this Sunday, December 8th at 3pm and Monday, December 9th at 7:00 pm in the JDHS auditorium. Tickets will be sold at the door beginning at 2:30 on Sunday and 6:30 pm on Monday at a cost of $5.00 per person. Please come out and support your local Drama Club! Thank you!!! Contact Drama Advisor, Mrs. Tina Clay, with any questions at tina.clay@jeff-davis.k12.ga.us.

Synopsis: Two wealthy orphan girls must spend time with their only living relatives, hillbillies from Lone Mule, Tennessee, as a stipulation of their father's will. The girls, who are used to luxuries, are miserable as their Uncle tries to make them leave and give up their portion of the inheritance so he can inherit. He shows the girls the very worst of hillbilly life, but things don't always go as planned.

post_text: Great fishing on the Altamaha.
shared_text:
Wildlife Resources Division - Georgia DNR
September 30, 2013 at 4:09 PM ·

Fisheries staff collected this channel catfish while conducting their annual catfish population survey the Altamaha River last week. This year has been a banner year for channel catfish on the Altamaha, as we have had the highest catch rates observed in over 20 years! The average size of fish has also been very good, with many fish in the 14-18 inch range. Anglers are currently reporting catching many of these channel catfish along with good catches of bluegill from the river. Get your fishing license at http://georgiawildlife.com/licenses-permits-passes and try your own luck on the Altamaha soon!

Hazlehurst-Jeff Davis County Chamber of Commerce
September 16, 2013 at 3:22 PM ·

Jeff Davis Yellow Jackets will host the Tigers of Metter for the homecoming football game on Friday, October 4, 2013. The Chamber of Commerce is once again issuing a challenge to ALL merchants and businesses to support the 2013 Homecoming activities and show your “Jacket Pride.” Decorate your store front or lawn to support the football team, cheerleaders and band students. Please call the Chamber office at 375-4543 to register no later than 4:00pm on Wednesday, October 2nd. There is NO entry fee and judging will be done by senior class students. Decorations must be in place no later than 1:00pm on Thursday, October 3rd in order to be judged. The business demonstrating the most school spirit and “Jacket Pride” will be presented with a trophy to be displayed at their business for one year. Sisters’ Kountry Kitchen has won the contest for the last two years and has enjoyed the trophy and bragging rights. Let’s be creative and get “ready to rumble.”

September 16, 2013 at 3:22 PM ·

Jeff Davis Yellow Jackets will host the Tigers of Metter for the homecoming football game on Friday, October 4, 2013. The Chamber of Commerce is once again issuing a challenge to ALL merchants and businesses to support the 2013 Homecoming activities and show your “Jacket Pride.” Decorate your store front or lawn to support the football team, cheerleaders and band students. Please call the Chamber office at 375-4543 to register no later than 4:00pm on Wednesday, October 2nd. There is NO entry fee and judging will be done by senior class students. Decorations must be in place no later than 1:00pm on Thursday, October 3rd in order to be judged. The business demonstrating the most school spirit and “Jacket Pride” will be presented with a trophy to be displayed at their business for one year. Sisters’ Kountry Kitchen has won the contest for the last two years and has enjoyed the trophy and bragging rights. Let’s be creative and get “ready to rumble.”

Do you need a canoe to join the Fall Paddle and Rivers Alive Cleanup on October 5? Scott Taylor will rent you one for a special price of $35/day and take care of dropping you off and picking you up, where needed. If you've ever wanted to paddle the Altamaha, then this is your chance. It will be a somewhat short trip from Hinson's Landing to Towns Bluff Park and Heritage Center/RV Park and Campground. You can do your civic duty along the way by gathering up trash that you find along the river, too! Contact Scott Taylor at 912-245-0193 FMI. www.explorethreerivers.com

Jeff Davis Ledger
July 9, 2013 at 11:59 AM ·

The Jeff Davis County Commission has a called meeting set for Thursday, July 11, at 10 a.m. in the commissioners meeting room.
Items on the agenda are:
1. Approve pauper burial.
2. Approve resolution appointing a legislative coordinator.
3. Approve a resolution supporting the Board of Education bond resolution.
4. Approve a resolution regarding a lease purchase agreement for the purpose of procuring an ambulance.
5. Approve work detail agreements for Jeff Davis County and Towns Bluff Park.
6. Discus “ING” a joint feasibility study.
7. Closed session to discuss personnel.
